{
  "texts": [
    "I. INTRODUCTIONLarge Language Models (LLMs) have revolutionized the field of artificial intelligence by providing unprecedented capabilities in natural language processing, yet their effectiveness hinges significantly on the precision of information retrieval, critical in applications where the integrity of the information provided directly impacts decision-making processes and knowledge dissemination [1], [2], [3].",
    "The integration of deep learning techniques has been a driving force in the advancement of LLMs, offering powerful tools for pattern recognition and data interpretation [4].",
    "However, the incorporation of symbolic reasoning presents an opportunity to further enhance the capabilities of LLMs, particularly in terms of logical deduction and rule-based processing, areas where deep learning alone may falter [5].",
    "This novel approach promises to amalgamate the intuitive pattern recognition of deep learning with the structured, rule-based logic of symbolic reasoning, potentially leading to a more robust and accurate information retrieval system within LLMs [4], [5].",
    "A. BackgroundThe current landscape of LLMs is marked by their impressive language understanding and generation abilities, which have been extensively demonstrated in various applications ranging from automated text generation to complex questionanswering systems [2]."
  ]
}